      "side": 1,
      "message": "while i like the functions encapsulating higher level functionality, i\u0027m not a fan of how often we keep rescanning the environ array.\n\nsemi-terrible idea.  what if getenv_index API was:\n\n // Returns true if |name| is found, false if not.\n // If found, |i| is |name|\u0027s index.  If not found, |i| is the length.\n bool getenv_index(char **envp, const char *name, *int i);\n\nthen we wouldn\u0027t have double scanning in these helpers.  we\u0027d still have double scanning across multiple calls, but we have that today, and might be a little harder to avoid when we have to scan the array names anyways.",
      "revId": "3f2eed4258edfc30e2c1190f144d8ff370a0413c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
